betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§5§lWE HAVE MANAGED TO ESCAPE THE SHATTERED HUSK OF OUR PREVIOUS HOME DIMENSION! WE NOW STAND UPON THE PRISTINE PLAINS OF-

PLAINS.. §rof...?

§l§fHang on, am I a BOOK? Why am I a §obook? §o§rLast thing I remember was running for the portal after you guys destroyed the world §o- §othanks§r for that, by the way. Now I'm a book. Great. No world, no ARMS, no HAIR? UGH. I need to go deal with this, for now, that redoubt seems safe.

Okay, fine. I'm a book. I've never been a book before, but hey, beats being dead! This is still your fault, but since I don't have hands, you'll have to do the heavy lifting for us. You know the drill, new world, no tools or anything so

§5§lGO PUNCH A TREE.

Okay, so apparently I can summon items sometimes. Not just §oanything§o§r, but it might help. Can't give the magic book too much agency, I guess. *grumble*

One other thing I've noticed is that the days here are longer than in our previous world - which is weird, because the nights are the same length. Handy for growing, if nothing else. You'll want to assemble those parts I gave you into some tools at the smithy, it should be here somewhere.

Hey, nice digs! I mean, it's no SKY ORB, but considering everything we used to know is blasted ex-dimension shards, we should take what we can get. According to my (further) research, §5§lTHIS WORLD HAS TRUE DARKNESS.

§rThat is, previously, there was always a certain amount of background light - torches, lamps, what have you. Here? If there's no light source, there's §ono light.§r Something to keep in mind when out and about, for sure. We should also §l§5§lMAKE SOME TORCHES TO LIGHT UP THE AREA§r, hey? Looks like they're made the usual way - jam a stick into some coal or charocal.

Speaking of torches! §5§lIN THIS WORLD, TORCHES BURN BRIGHTLY, YET BRIEFLY.§r *cough* Man, talking like that is hard on my... throat? That doesn't even make SENSE! Blah blah blah torches burn out and you can relight them with matches, or by cooking them in a furnace. Or you could if you had HANDS. Gah! Go wrestle a zombie or something.

...in my defense, I didn't know that zombies were resistant to normal swords until just after you left. But now, I've learned? Learned, sure. I've §olearned§r that §l§5§lIN THIS LAND, THE RESTLESS DEAD CAN BE SMITED BY FIRE OR HOLY BLADE. §r"Holy" apparently equals "silver" in this case. You'll need a silver blade, unless you want to keep just chipping away at a zombie until it dies.

Now that we've got things figured out (more or less), we should head out into the world and start building! The redoubt is nice and all to visit, but do you want to live here? Besides, I want to see more of this world, and it's not like §oI§r can walk there.

Before you go, you should §5§lmake an atlas§r to map the world as you travel. You'll be able to mark down where this place is and other points of interest inside it, which will help keep you from getting utterly lost.

You handle putting together a book and I'll manage the mapping part - you'll be able to find all the resources you need in or near this place, I bet.

Well, my old sky fortress and whatever garbage hole you lived in are gone.  Probably forever, but that's just the spite speaking.   Regardless, you need to get on making a place for me to live and you to keep working for me.


§l§d§lSo how to go about getting a nice place to live, hm?

§l§5
§5§fWell, a hole in the dirt or rock is the poor garbage man's way, but as a concerned book, how about not.   Let's maybe try to use those planks to build us a nice-ish thing to not die in.   Moving past that, we'll need some basic niceties to have a real home in hell.   

§l§5§lBring me some wood which I will somehow change into doors to keep you safe, and a furnace for me to cozy while you mosey.

I have good news! This place isn't full of nothing but zombies, skeletons, and god only knows what else which wants to feast on your brains.

Cows, sheep, pigs, horses, and a pretty wide variety of nonhostile animals are around; some are even useful.

You should make some decently sized pens for them if you want to get into animal husbandry.§5 §lFive by five should do.

In your travels so far, I'm sure you've seen those little gardens hanging around and even broken a few. If not, no big deal.

Those gardens contain seeds which will expand your gustatory horizons and allow you to do more than just chow down on piles of bread. That said, we'll need a recipe book so you don't get overwhelmed with options!

Once you do that, I'll get us some gardens so you can get seeds. You can also farm these gardens by placing them down on grass and waiting a bit, so I'd break two to get seeds and keep one planted for later.  Do note you can sneak-break a garden, either these or wild ones, to pick them up in once piece.

Also, did you know you can sell off any spare crops to the Market? Neat!

And now, with the idea of a varied diet planted in your head, it's time for some bad news. Well, neutral news.

§5§lEating nothing but bread is bad for you.§r

Sure, it's filling and better than cured zombie meat, but you aren't really §oliving§r if the only thing you eat is bread. So, I present the proverbial carrot:

§5§lFor each of the primary nutritional values you keep above 80%, your health will increase by 20%.§r

Those values, by the way, are Protein, Dairy, Grain, Fruit, and Vegetable. You can see what you're at through the carrot icon in your inventory.

Huh, looks like that burger has some additional values attached to it. Let's see...Savory? Salt? What?

Oh.

§5§lFor each Flavor value above 80%, you'll get a special ability.§r

§cSpicy§r foods will help you resist heat, §eSweet§r foods will give you an energy boost, §7Salty§r foods will boost your strength, §aQuenchy§r foods will help you stay cool, §bBitter§r foods will help you resist damage, and §6Savory§r foods will increase your endurance.

There's no penalty for having these values, or the Nutrients from before, at a low level. It's all gravy!

It's interesting that the stars here are the same as anywhere else. More interesting that they have magical power.

That resonating wand looks to be the key to harnessing that power - something about crystals? I'll see if I can shortcut hunting around at bedrock for them.

Well, good, now that we've figured out a base of operations we can §oreally§o§r get to work. Make sure you've had a nap in your bed and let's get cracking.

Well, YOU will. I'll just ride along in your backpack or something.

First things first, we're going to need to get some basic minerals. Iron and Copper should do.§5§l

STRIKE THE EARTH!

Those troughs imply that you'll need to keep your animals fed and watered. The good news on that is most of the ones you'll want in large quantities - goats, chickens, peafowl, sheep, cows, horses, and rabbits - can manage one or both on their own if they have access to a natural water source and grass.

By my calculations, a grassy pen with a two block by two block water source can support two animals pretty much indefinitely. Salt Licks will heal some kinds of farm animals.

Huh, so these guys drop...pieces of a talisman? Try and get all four, then slot them into their altar and see what you get - or just borrow one from a friend, I'm not picky.

If I'm right, you can use this Swamp Talisman with a sapling to make a portal to...somewhere else. 

...

§5§lYou may not want to bring any tools or food from this dimension with you. They might react strangely, or just be useless.

§rThis Akashic Tome will probably be useful later, to help you keep your guidebooks and whatnot organized.

betterquesting:10.name:8: All We Wanna Do is Hoard Your Brains
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Or, in this case, your crystallized magical essence. Whatever those Druids have been up to, it's locked most magic away in the Betweenlands, and the concentration of it is so thick it's not only impregnated the native metals and crystals, but also deposited right out of the air as elemental crystals.

Go grab a few - at least three - and let's see what we can do with them. §5§lMake sure to take a nap before doing any experiments§r. You'll want to be rested so you can run the fuck away if things go bad.

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's Just a Jump to the Left, and a Step to the Right
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
It's not much of a trip to find this stuff, either. The Betweenlands are chock full of magica and it's infused into a variety of different crystalline and metallic ores.

This stuff seems to be a different form of pure magic, which you can use to directly power previously created spells.

§5§lIf there are any other Wizards in the Overworld, they might trade some of this stuff for knowledge.

betterquesting:10.name:8: A Stern Rebuke of The Eldritch
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§b§lThe Betweenlands§r. A murky world of swamps and strange magics, this place is the end result of delving too deep and too greedily into power for its own sake.

The beasts here are dangerous, and if you find yourself faced with the likes of a Peat Mummy? §4§lRUN.§r

There are new resources here, as well, and I'm certain we can harness them somehow. You know the drill - §5§lpunch a tree§r.

Keep in mind this place is as strange to me as it is to you. Here's what I know:

1.) Plants, minerals, and some parts of creatures have magical properties, or §bAspects§r. These are useful in a new kind of Alchemy called §bInfusion§r.

2.) Tools and weapons crafted from materials here have a tendency to §aCorrode§r when exposed to the damp air, which is pretty much any time you're carrying them here. Corrosion can be reversed in a Purifier or staved off with a coating of Scabyst.

3.) The damp, sickly air here also affects §oyou§r, §eDecay§ring your body as time passes. You'll need to prevent it by chewing some gummy sap or bitter flowers.

4.) Food from the swamp wears on you and gets §cboring over time§r. It's a good idea to swap things up every twenty meals or so. Most foods from the Overworld, with the exception of fried insects, are inedible while exploring the swamps.

5.) There's a circle of interaction between some kind of special gem, which you can apply to tools and weapons. §3Aqua§r beats §4Crimson§r beats §2Green§r, in a loop.
There's a strange...resonance between these two ores. You should break some and take them home with you, if you can.

betterquesting:10.name:8: A Deal With the Essence of the World
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
So you wrote a book in the middle of a strange dream about those crystals? You better be careful this world doesn't get shredded like the last one.

Anyway, this stuff might be called "Mundane Salt" but it's positively teeming with magic. Do as the weird dream-book suggests and make some, then sprinkle it on a Bookshelf. We might get something interesting out of it.

Booyah, time to make steel. Now, you've got a couple options here.

First one is to grind up Iron and Charcoal in that Drill Grinder you made, and combine it with some Marble to make Steel Blend, which you can melt down and cast into an Ingot. You won't get a great return - something like 4:1 - but it'll get you making steel without needing to set up power and logistics and all that.

The §o§mfun§r§oefficient§r way is going to be making a Coke Oven and then a Blast Furnace, though you'll need to grind down Netherrack and Sandstone into Sulfur and Nitrate, respectively, for the Furnace. This'll get you a 1:1 Iron:Steel ratio, which is cool and good.

Let me know when you've got a decent amount of Steel.

Before you get into generating power, you should set up some batteries to store what you don't use. Capacitors are a good starting point, and you'll need one for Energy Cells as well.

PRO TIP: You can pass electrical wiring through walls by way of a Feedthrough Insulator. Place connectors horizontally on either side of a solid block, and boop one of the connectors with a hammer.

Well, it looks like we - you - have a few more steps to take to get to fulfilling your Randian fantasies. As great as Copper and Iron are, they're not going to be able to hold up to the stresses of steam power or mass excavation - and we can't do either of those yet, anyway.

Good news is I think we can make some basic machinery that runs off of the ambient magic around us. So there's that.

Also, these bonsai pots will make life a little easier - less manual tree farming!

Ah, good old Steel. That's our production line adventures half done. The other half is Plastic, and let me tell you, there's enough ways to produce it to make my head spin - and I don't have a head!

Method 1 is slow and doesn't need much power, but sucks to automate - just slap a Latex Processing Unit§r down next to a tree and give it some juice to get a little Dry Rubber§r. Problem is you'll have to smash nine of the little bastards together to get a chunk big enough to be of any use once you cook it.

Method 2 is a bit easier to automate, and uses a Sawmill§r with a Resin Funnel§r upgrade to produce Resin alongside Planks and Sawdust. You'll need to process it further into Rosin§r and then cook that into Plastic§r.

Method 3 involves different ways of making Tar§r and cooking it into Plastic§r, ranging from processing Oil Sand§r in a Pulverizer§r equipped with a Tectonic Initiator§r, to pulverizing and liquefying Coal§r, to making Biodiesel§r and processing it down into Tar§r - or just distilling Crude Oil§r down into Tar§r.

Just §5§lCHECK THAT BOX§r and we'll move on.

Moving chests and machines can suck, so I did a little research and it turns out the native magical properties of this world makes it fairly easy to move stuff around without losing your shit.

Strap a few sticks and some metal together, presto, a chest transporter! This can also move single-block machinery around without losing its settings, which is useful.

Speaking of moving while carrying things, I've got a satchel with your name on it.

Of course, if you want something high-current and reliable, you'll need to upgrade.

Options are different kinds of dynamo, diesel generators, or steam turbines. Thermoelectric generators are possible too, if you have the space.

No matter which you choose, that low-power capacitor won't cut it. Make us something with a little more oomph, wouldja?
And that point is §ooptions.§r Trees are renewable and a lot less infrastructure-heavy than oil refining, so if you wanna §ago green§r and just chill, man, hook us all up with some Rosin.

It might not matter to you, but I think it's worth mentioning that you can make the basic frames for more compact machines now, and more efficient power storage. These §odo§r use power, so if you want to caveman it out these probably aren't very useful, but still - make one of each. I'm sure you'll find §osome§r use for them later.

Of course, if you'd rather not bother with a tool that also makes you slower while you carry stuff, there are options.

Storage Crates can be picked up without dropping their contents, and by default store as much as a normal chest.

Strongboxes and Caches can also be picked up without dropping their contents. Strongboxes initially store a little less than crates do, but can hold up to three times as much before you even get into messing with the Holding enchantment.

Caches are a way to do mass storage, and at base level hold 20k items. At max upgrade, without enchantments, they can hold 500k.

Keep in mind that Crates used for crafting will §onot§r retain their contents!

Of course, if you like to §osee§r your hoard, a wall full of drawers is the way to go. At their most, drawers hold 7168 stacks, or slightly less than a Resonant Cache.

However, Drawers have customizable looks and plain old §ostyle§r in spades, so I can't blame you for using them instead of Caches.

If you're a fan of efficient mass production, this is how you roll. It doesn't matter if you produce it from crude oil, liquid coal, or oil sands - tar is tar, and we can make that tar into plastic. You get this machine put together and I'll throw in some extra goodies.

You're going to need something to make that power, of course, so here's your chance.

Windmills and waterwheels will at least get us beyond relying on the interaction of magic and metal, so slam one down and get generating.

One thing you should know by now is that everything has some sort of use. I have a feeling we'll need to go deeper into Hell, literally, if you want to take technology as far as you can.

Grab some Quartz and Netherrack, then get home before something eats you.

The end of your storage problems, guaranteed.

Well, okay, not all by itself but you've done this enough to understand that after this CPU comes the disk drives and whatnot. Make sure you have enough power for everything you set up and you'll be golden.

By the way, you're not limited to solid-run wires.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Best Packs Live On In Memory
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
By now you should have pretty stable power for all your shit. If that's so, check the box.

Remember that Bad Things will happen to you if it turns out you don't and your fuckups ruin things for everyone else.

betterquesting:10.name:8: I Will Not Waste Your Time
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The Arc Furnace is neat, right? Yep. Thing is, you don't strictly need one to make this stuff - although it is the most efficient way, and probably the one you actually have access to.

Anyway, §5§lget some Dark Steel ingots and let's have ourselves a digital revolution.

And sometimes it's not, but being able to make plastic opens up a lot of automation options, so I think it's worth the effort.

Now, I assume that in going for this stuff you're going to want to set up an automated slaughterhouse, so if you don't mind I'll make things easier for you once you prove you can make plastic.

And I'm not going to squawk about it if you skip all the machinery stuff you don't like to get to the stuff you §odo§r like.

Get some Dry Rubber, I'll double it, and we'll get on with things.

If that direction is exploration, you'll probably want your homestead to keep chugging along while you're away. This gadget, using a little more of the residual magic around here, will ensure a shape and size of your choosing will stay loaded during your absence.

Do note that each person's ability to channel this magic through their works is limited; as best I can calculate, each loader can channel enough power to hold 25 chunks in unending active state, with anything made by you having a global limit of 30.

You can craft spot loaders to do single chunks for precision and efficiency.

If you take a break, your homestead will stay loaded for four hours before the gadget winds down. You'll be able to spin it back up by coming back online.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Now Put Your Hands on Your Hips, and Bring Your Knees in Tight
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
As with most other forms of magic, you will need a tool for focus and direct spells you cast.

Naturally, wizards use wands, and this basic one will let you get started on your road to mastering this form of magic.

I'm not entirely sure what this powder is, but I have a feeling we'll need it later. Create this stuff by grabbing an §bIron Focusing Rod§r, throwing some redstone into the world, and right-clicking with the Rod.

My guess is it's a kind of distilled magic, which we'll be able to use in other items.

And, as usual, we'll need a workbench to go with the wand. This one will let you apply upgrades to the wand and recharge it, as well as set which spells the wand is able to cast.

Thankfully, those spells can be swapped in and out as needed. §5§lYou'll need to go exploring and delve dungeons to get more spells, or trade with a friendly wizard.

§5§lMe personally, I've never been a huge reader.

§oWhich is kind of ironic, given.

§rBut these things we've seen here have made me think, and I'm certain you are too. Might as well crack this tome open and see what we can learn.

You ever thought to yourself, on a day you are so bored you're staring at a wall for entertainment: "I wonder if this wall has anything more to it?"

§5§lI mean, you would, wouldn't you, wall-person. :V

§rEntirely beside the point as that is, your idle thought brought on by either excessive pizza or ADHD were actually in one way correct.   Walls, ground, the dirt you walk on, pocket change even, *do* actually have another set of properties.

The practice of thaumaturgy is a way to gain that insight, with an odd modification of a microscope known as a "Thaumometer".  Utilizing it to look closer at things can show you these hidden properties, and allow you to find uses for stuff you had otherwise written off, like that mixtape you made for Chelsea in Grade 7, Eric.

§5§lGet yourself the newest magitechical science gizmo, maybe we can see if §oyou§r§5§l have another use besides the already lacking void.     


I'm kidding.


§oMostly.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Allo The Mancies In The World
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Fascinating. It seems that if you grind metals up and stick them in a glass bottle made from the silt of the Betweenlands, you can ingest the resulting slurry to gain special powers.

Copper flakes allow you to see the metal magic - §b§lAllomancy§r - of others, while Bronze hides your own magic. Iron and Steel allow you to pull and push at metals in the world - you could use this to spiderman around, or to fire gold nuggets at enemies. Tin gives you the ability to see at night, and detect nearby motion via sound, while Pewter boosts your metabolism something fierce. Zinc and Brass allow you to Riot or Soothe mobs, working them into a frenzy or making hostile mobs passive - even fearful.

Hm, interesting. Apparently, Nightshade is §omore§r than just a poison. At full growth, it seems to attract, well, faeries.

Which you can capture in a glass bottle, then transfer to a Faerie Enclosure. I'm not sure what purpose this serves, but I can see hints of...some sort of altar, and a ring?

Fucko, we need to talk.  I can't actually see anything as a book, but aesthetics matter to me.

§5§lI deeply require exquisite, §4§llustful, §a§larchitecture.

§fSo with that in mind, how about you make a chisel, and start carving your face into it.  §6§6Somehow, from beyond this void of senses, I'll know, and I'll be so very, very...

§fWait, what was I talking about?   Right, chisels, aesthetics.


§oDefinetly not experiencing attraction as a book.

§o§hNow, how's about you make a nice ol' chiselin' thing?

§5§lWell, you've gone and done it, haven't you?§r

§kYou've invoked the hive-mind representing Chaos.
Invoked the feeling of Chaos without Order.
Drawn the attention of the Nezperdian hive-mind of Chaos: ZALGO!
He Who Waits Behind The Wall.
ZALGO!§r

This Warp stuff is bad news - it's messing with your head and making you act strange. It's even affecting me! Look at that!

I - §o§owe§r - need to get rid of this, pronto. There's bound to be some sort of purifying soap...
Having to run back to your workroom every time you need to recharge your wizard's wand, that is. Thankfully, you can bottle those mana crystals and take them with you as a convenient consumable.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Point of One so Floo-lish
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
As it happens, combining Psidust with an Enderpearl makes Floo Dust. This will let you connect a lit fireplace to a network of lit fireplaces, and use some powder to teleport across the network.

This will make it easier to say hi to goonpals!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Let's Do The Time Warp Again
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Speaking of other wizards, there are some who will not trade and prefer to hoard their knowledge, attacking anyone who intrudes on their towering holdfasts.

If you find one, you might as well kill him - you won't get anything from him otherwise.

Somewhere among the sludge and slime are Tar Pools. From those pools arise horrific beasts, made from animate tar.

According to my research, if we're to figure out the darkness engulfing the Betweenlands, §5§lwe need the heart of a Tar Beast.§r

Equip yourself appropriately - I recommend ranged weapons - then §4§lfind and destroy one of these hideous monsters.

betterquesting:10.name:8: For The World We Have Lost
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
You're going to need to go beyond the limitations of Thaumaturgy and Wizard's spells if we want to ensure that this world doesn't get ruined like the old one did.

§5§lIt's time to delve into the creation of our own spells and magical effects.§r

To get started, we'll need something to focus those spells - let's call it a rod. Unsurprisingly, you'll need a specialized crafting table to hold everything in alignment while you work.

§o"Not to be confused with a Peat Mummy, an already vicious creature of pure malice found in Marshes and Sludge Plains.

This thing is infested with the essence of an impossible demon, which has ripped it partially open and grown three monstrous legs from the back of the beast, dragging the dreadful corpse around as it hunts for victims.

None should have to face it."§r

Bad news, then. You need to. I don't know why, but §5§lthis thing needs to die.§r Make some Mummy Bait and drop it on the ground anywhere you might run into the lesser version.

§4§lThen, end the monster. Good luck.

The key now is to make something which we can use to actually put spells together. I'll call it an §5§lInscriber.

Make one.

betterquesting:10.name:8: What Was, Will Be; What Will Be, Was
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
These are the parts you will need for the most powerful spells that we can create - spells which affect not only space but time.

Take care in your explorations, and try not to destroy the world, okay?

betterquesting:10.name:8: In the Name of Magic and Materialism
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Warp, Flux, Taint...ugh! It's enough to make me sick.

You're going to need defenses against all sorts of nasty stuff and if it's magic, you'll want magic armor. This Fortress Armor seems like it'll do the trick.
If you're a fan of rituals and passive magic, give totems a try. I don't have all the details, but this other book probably does.

As useful as golems are, they're rather delicate and somewhat unreliable as guards go. I think we can apply the same technology to make bigger, stronger brethren: Gargoyles.

This specialized pumpkin is the brain of the beast, and making one is fairly simple: A T-shape of different materials with the pumpkin stuck atop will result in a self-propelled skullfuck for anything hostile that gets too close. The question is what materials?

Lucky you, I have a list of shapes to try.

1. Redstone base with iron core and stone arms.
2. Redstone base with sandstone core and arms. 
3. Diamond base and core with obsidian arms.
4. Diamond base and core with gold arms.
5. Redstone base with gold core and iron arms.
6. Redstone base with gold core and endstone arms
7. Redstone base with gold core and nether brick arms.

betterquesting:10.name:8: A Little Help from My Hens
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Ah, flight. The dream of mankind since time began. Lucky for us, the transitive property of magic means that you can encase a feather in magically-infused metals to gain the power of flight.

It is, however, limited to a modest range around any active beacon.

Technically you can also strip the world of ore with Laser Drills, but those are slow and you just don't get the same visceral feeling watching a pile of ore turn into more ingots that you know what to do with.

After this, the world's literally your oyster. Go forth and stock up.

Frankly, I'm one to complain.  

§l§4§lAbout bullshit like magical zombies that don't learn to die.


§fWell, we know how to kill the things, but that one stick and a silver slab won't last. 


What you need is a workshop of sorts.   I think we both know how this goes down otherwise.   Toolless, constantly remaking breakable pisstakes.


§4§lHorrifying.§f

Well, we have our wood.  We have your hands and work ethic, and my unending pit of sarcasm.   Get those pattern slabs up, slap them on top of things and violate physics like we always have.

betterquesting:10.name:8: A Familiar Pile of Blackened Brick
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
You know, I remember our first smeltery.   I say "our" with some apprehension, as I can't actually tell which person I landed with as a book.   If it's you Etente, I still want my 50 quid.  If it's YOU 5Alive, you are not, and never were above the law.


Aside my reminiscience, we should do it all over, for what may be the umpteenth time.   If you take the usual pile of gravel, dump sand on it, dump clay on that, do a dance on top of that disgusting pile, it turns into even more disgusting grout.   It's AWFUL.

§9§lSo we're skipping the usual.


§f
Just get those individual parts, and I'll do Book Magic™ to make everything better.  I don't know when I learned this stuff, but hey, maybe better not to know.

§c§4§lYou know, we've been through a lot.§f

I don't know how much our old home has crossed your mind these days, it's been a distant memory for a fair while even for me.

But the world we've found here doesn't deserve it's fate, and neither does any other.

That being said, the energies of that portal which ate our world are back.  Don't ask me how I can tell, it's just a thing I'm able to do. Apparently. 

More importantly, someone or some§othing §ris bringing these energies to bear, and we're not going to be able to ignore it any longer.

I think I can eventually pinpoint the source, but I had another request of sorts.

We don't know what lives in the Swamp we found behind those tree portals, on the one hand it seems nothing sapient might, but I'm erring on the side of empathy here.  I want to make sure what happened to us can't happen there, and while I may have once said we need to focus on our own problems, I believe with what we've gained from this world it falls to our shoulders to fix what other cannot.

§4§l§5§lWe need to end the threat the Betweenlands faces. Deep in its swamps lies a temporally displaced Fortress, trapped and infested with the worst that the murk can muster.§f

§rWe need to go there, and solve its puzzles, defeat its guards, and end the influence of what can only be called a living form of Malevolence.  Reading though knowledge we've gained over our adventures and advances tells me of a specific sword we'll need to find in the Fortress to defeat this entity.  Then fight our way to the roof, where we should be able to draw it out of its tear in reality to kill it.


While the temporal displacement means killing one may leave yet another, the lack of uniformity will lead to the other's deaths eventually.  Such is the will of causality.

§b§lGodspeed to us.

In addition to chiseling blocks for style, there's a selection of rustic materials we can use to spruce things up around here. Wood's nice, but stone is a bit more solid, and plain wood planks just lack something.

§5§lSee what you can scrounge up to make your hovel a bit nicer.

There are five kinds of chicken around these parts: Leghorn, Oprington, Plymouth Rock, Rhode Island Red, and Wyandotte. They're pretty much identical in function, but to make them lay eggs you'll need a nest for each hen.

You'll have to manually throw seeds on the ground to feed them, but they'll drink from troughs or ponds automatically.

There are a full 9 kinds of cow in this world, split into two groups: Milk and Beef.

Milk Cows are the Holstein, Friesian, and Jersey breeds. They produce milk which can be made into cheese, but have to be kept happy or pregnant to produce milk.

Beef Cows are the Angus, Hereford, Texas Longhorn, and Scottish Highland breeds. These cows also produce milk, but drop specialized beef cuts when happy instead of prime-grade milk.

Both kinds of cow will feed and water themselves from Troughs, or from grass and ponds. Cows will eat wheat and red or yellow flowers.

Draft Horses are a specialized kind of workhorse, able to pull wagons around. They're found where you'd normally expect to find horses.

Draft Horses will feed and water themselves from Troughs, or from grass and ponds. They will eat wheat, apples, and carrots.

Goats are the most robust and useful herd animal, since they provide milk, wool, §oand§r meat to the dedicated herder. Seven kinds of Goat exist, all of which are functionally the same despite being found in different biomes.

Goats can feed and water themselves from Troughs, or from grass and ponds. Goats will eat apples, beets, carrots, sticks, string, and wheat.
Pewafowl are a jungle and swamp equivalent of chickens, and there are 7 kinds whose main difference is color. Caring for Peafowl is mostly identical to caring for Chickens.

As with the rest of the animals, there's multiple breeds of pig, and unsurprisingly they're pretty much all identical in function. Pigs are able to water and feed themselves from Troughs, or from grass and ponds. Pigs will eat beets, carrots, potatoes, and slop.

Pigs can be ridden using a carrot tied to a stick, and adult pigs can be used to hunt for Truffles in forests. You can ensure the happiness of your pigs by giving them a muddy area to roll around in.

All these little guys are good for is meat, hides, and feet. There are 8 breeds, but they're pretty much identical.

Rabbits will feed and hydrate themselves from grass and ponds. They'll also eat carrots from your hand.

As with the rest, there are multiple varieties of Sheep. They're mostly the same except for the raw color of their wool.

Sheep will eat and drink from Troughs, or from grass and ponds. They will eat wheat, carrots, and beets.

In addition to herd animals, there are some which serve no purpose except to make §oyou§r happy by being silly balls of fur. You can find Ferrets, Hamsters, and Hedgehogs around the world, and tame them by feeding them something they like.

None of these animals can be bred yet, and they don't drop anything useful either. With the exception of Hamsters, they are able to handle their own feeding and hydration, though not from Troughs.

Ferrets will eat eggs or mutton. Hedgehogs will eat eggs, carrots, or beets. Both will steal eggs from chicken nests, and Hedgehogs will dig up beets or carrots to feed themselves.

Hamsters only eat Hamster food, but they can use a Hamster Wheel to make a little power.

So, the strange thing is, there's a kind of residual magic in this world, right? I've done some thinking and it seems to be centered on swamps, and these Dark Druid guys who you might find there.

§5§lGo beat them up and take their stuff.

§r§o(If you have trouble finding a swamp, I hear there's a merchant who'll sell you something which lets you summon one.)

§5§lReally, I should have known better than to leave it completely up to you to intuit everything.


§rStorage drawers are pretty great, but they can't be moved with stuff in them, leaving you unable to adapt. §6§l§r§4§lOR SO YOU THOUGHT.

§rIntroducing Packing Tape, slap some on a drawer full of as many items as you can get away with and they'll never fall out.  Until you remove it, but the job's done by then right?

(As a note, Chest Transporters will work too, but Packing Tape is better - you won't get tired and you can carry more than one drawer at a time.)

There do seem to be some methods of creating specialized wands with more...§ophysical§r effects. These wands don't require any additional power source beyond the magic inherent in their cores, but can only perform a single task.

The most useful application is likely to be the magical placement and removal of blocks.

*yawn* Damn! I know it hasn't been that long since we arrived here but it feels like §3months.§f You've mastered machinery and magic (with the help of your impossibly handsome book of course), and it seems we're pretty well §oset§o.§f§r Time to kick back and rela-aaaagh what §o§l§c§lnow?

I didn't want to say anything earlier while I scouted what info I could, but the instant that conduit stopped accepting power... uh,  I got a reading of some sorts.


It's not an energy I recognize, and it's not in an area anybody we know lives.


This jungle ruin isn't too far from the redoubt either, and I'm starting to wonder what's going on here.


§5Proceed to it, keep an eye for weird changes or signs of inhabitation.   Probably underground.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Will You Missile Me When I'm Gone?
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Some of these metals look like they could be used for spacecraft construction, if alloyed properly. Gather some of them up and I'll show you some of what I learned before.

§c§lThis is insanity!   Crashing a station into our planet!?   What was I...§o me... §oTHINKING.§o§l§r§c§l §o§nJESUS TITS.§r


We need to find this thing, we need to take what we already had for space preparations and accelerate our plans...

Now that you have the infrastructure and the spacesuit, you'll of course need to build a spaceship. First step, build a §5rocket assembly machine.§r You'll need to provide it with power, as well as §5nine concrete blocks§r, and §5four structure towers§r. That's a minimum - you can use more. The concrete blocks form the landing pad, and the towers, comprise the gantry. Your spaceship can only be as big as what can fit on the pad and under the gantry.

To build a rocket, basically construct whatever shape you want. There are only a few things that §omust§r be included in a rocket:

§5A seat.
A guidance computer.
A Planet ID chip.
At least one rocket engine.
At least one fuel tank.

§rYour rocket engines have to provide enough thrust to overcome the weight of the rocket - it can be tricky to find a balance. Good luck, spacegoon!

§cI'd say I don't know what I was thinking.

§lI'd say that, and I'd be right.

§rWe're going to end this today.  We've found my station, we can get to it, we can shut down it's defences, overload it's grid, and pierce the heart to where the third part of myself remains.

All that remains is to end the station before it's descent can eradicate this world.

This will inevitably kill the part of me that resides inside.



I don't know what happens then.   I would lie, give a sarcastic quip and say just do it.

But I won't lie.

I'm afraid.

I don't know what happens when a part of me ceases to be.  Will we recoalesce?  Will the me among you and myself the book cease to be as time collapses our dissonant form?

While I have no answers to these, I do have a different answer.

And that is, end this.   The world here deserves better.  Our old home deserves better.

You, deserve better.

Myself, and myself will take what comes.

The show will go on.
Now that you have a spacesuit, a rocket, and a means to launch it, all you need is rocket fuel. Good luck and goonspeed!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Together, at The End of All Things
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§9Okay man, I uh..  I don't say this often, but this is freaking me out.


§bI recognize this.

§rI don't remember a thing about it, nor do I have any idea where this is, but it's not just leery deja-vu. §c§o I've been here at some point.


§r§5We need to know what's inside. §r Please, something doesn't feel right, and I want to be out of the dark on this one.

§5Check this lab out, make sure to read or check anything you come across, someone has to have left hints somewhere.

§dWell, you did it.  You got seeds, you got food, you're alllll set right?

§fWell, not always.  It seems a fair few of you hate this shit called winter, and I'm not a fan either - even if paper lacks heat receptors, my binding gets stiff.

That said: There is a miracle workaround!

Greenhouse glass, when placed up to 7 blocks above farmland with room for both a crop and at least one air block, allows crops beneath it to IGNORE SEASONS. Grow your papayas in Grise Fjord in February, YOU DONT HAVE TO CURR.

That said, I have noticed a distinct lack of cactus for some people, and there's a way around this too.  When you fill a cauldron with water, you can add a dye to get 3 effective dyes.  While you may not get to craft §oeverything§r that §2Cactus Green§r and §9Lapis§r can, you do get far more bang for your plant buck as far as crafting a lot of dyed goods goes, and the combined §bCyan§r water dye is valid for greenhouse glass!

§d§lRealistically, I'm not gonna demand anything.   Have a couple cauldrons for dye mixing and a sample on me.
Also, you may have heard there's no air in space. You'll have to bring your own - fortunately, there's suits for that. §5Go ahead and make one.

We have info on what to look for, we have the infrastructure, and the means to get around.

§c§lIt's time to find the station ¿I? (still not getting used to that I swear) have set up to Armageddon this planet with.

§rFrom what we've learned through the books in the lab, he mentioned gravitational pull being a problem, §5so check around big gas giants, or maybe even black holes.


§rThe sooner we have a point of reference, the sooner I can calibrate a means of getting there.

§9§lYou know what we need?  Power.  You know how to get more?

§c§lSmashing stuff.

§rNot quite the way you'd initially think, mind.  I mean the smashing of subatomic loveliness.

It's time to get learning about nuclear power!

That said, it's a bit of a buildup, we don't just take the stuff we dug up and instantly be pumping the 50k RF/t outputs in a hot minute.  Most of the stuff we got actually has to be processed and recombined to be of any use.

So let's waste no time and get ourselves down the path of limitless power!

§5You handle the grinder and furnace, and I'll get us an isotope splitter.

With the recent advances in microcircuitry, there's all sorts of things you can do with programming. You can build computers! Hey, what are you doing with that zombie head? PUT THAT DOWN there's no call for §5freaky advanced necroscience§r here! Are you even listening?

And thus we have arrived.

It is time.


§4For dbz tier crazy.

§rSo fusion requires real work to setup.   §5You have your core,§r then structural pieces that are on each face of the core, minimum of 1 to 3 in length and then an enclosed pipe of electromagnets around that in contact with the structure, like a + of magnets with a hollow core.  When that is ready, you need to power all the magnets, and the core itself, with fuel to begin to heat it all.


Once you have spent this §aludicrous§r startup cost, fusion begins.  And it is here, that not only does it become§o self sustainin§r§og§r, but§l§o§b§l§o insanely profitable§r, energy wise.

Fuels range to a lot of options, but a simple one I can provide help with is smashing Helium with itself.

§4§lDo be aware that this helium producer is itself highly radioactive.  Please make sure you are ready before I give it to you.

Huh. That's.. actually pretty inventive. §c§lGROSS§r, but inventive. Is there anything along those lines you can do uh, §owithout§r getting your hands covered in brains? Maybe with ender pearls?

§o§1§2§o(I'm so glad books can't vomit)

§c§lI've heard you all complain about movement.

§fHow getting around is like sand.

Coarse, rough, and slow as the... wait a second.


§9§f§9§lNevermind my crazy non-sequiters.


WE GOT CARS NOW.

§fThat's right!  Somehow by the grace of the void and our own lack of impetus, there are actual factual vehicles you can make to do the get place thing better than ever!

§5
Whip up the needful workshop and I'll pull my old moped out of storage for you.
It looks like the merchant at the redoubt left - too weird for him, I guess. What's that thing he left behind though?
Instituting fiat currency without a mint? Ugh, how irresponsible. Give me a diamond and I'll convert it for you.

Say, I don't know about you, but uh, didn't our base used to §onot§r have all this smog and yellowish crap in it?

§c§lOh fuck, pollution has come for us!  Truly our hubris shall be our undoing!§1
§9
Well, okay, calm down.

§rWhat we have here is our own unchecked ambitions biting us in the ass a bit.   It seems from what I've observed, is that most machinery which burns stuff or grinds it, or really anything you think might have particulate outputs, well, §oactually did.


§rSulphur can even explode, so that's even less great than the already immediate threat of suffocating on land.

For now while I research means of mitigating this, take these tools to suck it all up Luigi style, and to breathe.

Whew, the immediate threat inside our house is done.

Now we turn to all the potential climate damage we may have already done.

§1§9§lIt seems that as we have more sulphur buildup, we can get acid rain and other adverse effects outside.

§rThere is a tool to view levels, but we have more pressing concerns for our interiors.

Anything that outputs these foul things can have their outputs collected via the wonder that is §lchimneys.  §rYou can connect chimneys to things that output through vents, and with pumps, you can add a redstone signal to even suck already existing pollutants to a chimney system.


But the problem remains of buildup, and that's where I have a great soltion: filters!

Just shove some wool over the chimney and it sucks up all the sulphur, easy peasy!  For carbon and dust it's a mite bit more work, combine your new filter with 3 leaves on an anvil to get a carbon filter, and 3 paper sheets for dust filters. 

§5§lIf you can get us the start of a ventilation system, I'll Book Magic™ up some basic filtration, and we can all breathe easy once more.

§rAt least until the oceans rise and drown us all.

betterquesting:10.name:8: When The Winds of Causality Blow
betterquesting:10.desc:8: "If you're reading this, then I am no longer."  Essentially, Neo is one non-evil person again.  Give everyone a pat on the back and tgood ol Thankye, Thats it till DPT: Sigma
The world is vast, and no one book can have seen it all. Go forth and explore!
You can now extract dyes from previously useless flowers. Weee!
With improved cloche technology, you can grow almost any kind of plant in a cloche now. This includes pretty flowers, rustic crops, and even those really gross plants from the Betweenlands.
There are some new things to be discovered in your thaumonomicon...
With the advent of even fancier materials technology, we can create tools even weirder and more powerful than ever before!
Now that you know how to store non-solids in the computer and also manipulate essentia on a basic level, why not combine those into a storage system any thaumaturge would drool over?

Alright, now, I don't know if you noticed, but, everywhere we look outside is littered with dead birds lately. I mean, we could hire a cleaning lady I guess, but that isn't how we do things, is it?

Instead, we will §o§9§o§9reach for the skies!§o§r Grasp the pollution we've been venting so carelessly, and pull it back down to where we can filter it out properly.

§l§5§lGet us a Pollution Pump, and I'll rustle up some Pipes to get it working.

§rFilters can be placed directly next to a pump to shove skyfarts into them if there is room, and the pump requires power to run.

I don't want to alarm you, but there are holes in the world now.

Not §odangerous§r ones -- I don't think? They seem more like your nether portals if nothing else. I'd suggest going to have a look. If you infuse a regular wooden door with some alchemist's salt and endermetal, you should be able to use that door on a rift. Leave me here please, dimensional travel makes me queasy.

It looks like there's a way to create a tool to harness rift energy to your own purposes. I'd suggest a wrench, but knowing how you work, I'll make you a sword. Just give me.. ten? Yeah, §l§5ten ender pearls§r. If you lose it you can make a new one, but it'll take some §odoing.§r
That's certainly an interesting array of items in the vending machine. Are those cybernetic implant blueprints? §6§o§lDO THEY HAVE ANY PARTS FOR BOOKS?!§r

§cNO§r,§r I'm not bitter about not getting upgrades. Why do you ask? Just because YOU can transcend your mortal form with chrome and casting doesn't mean §oI§o§r ever wanted enhanced cognition. Or cyber-arms. Or §cANY ARMS WHATSOEVER.§r

Just take your stupid trenchcoat and go, "Neo".
Your ancestors may have been dumb baby idiots who didn't understand matter, but there's no fundamental difference between solids and fluids, now is there? So why can't you store fluids in your PC?

The world is just §oexploding§r with possibility now - and again please do NOT take that literally. We stand at the dawn of a new era, and its wonders are manifold. Computers! Magitech! Motorized.. couches? Huh, this really is the modern day isn't it? Anyway, neat stuff. Go §a§ofind it.

Okay, this one is actually creeping me out a bit.

§9The Redoubt seems to have seen some action, and nobody we know is apparently the cause.   §r

That said, this seems less like it would have been a direct act, and more a shift in the land itself to reveal what was always hidden.

There's some machinery, just outside the place now, that must have been buried all this time.  It has some weird symbology, and an electrical port.   Best I can guess, we need to feed the sucker power for some reason.

It seems someone has finished feeding this thing it's inglorious appetite's desires.

For now, uh, we'll just keep trucking I suppose.

Second required quest for DPT.   To remain locked until such time as the actual station fight is ready.   Write something into the station quest about needing to wait for a teleporter frequency to open.

Now that the heavens have opened to you, it's time to start capitalizing on that. You'll want a §5station in near orbit§r to launch missions from, as well as a §5§5space elevator§r to simplify material transfer.

Once you have a feel for the local system of moons, you'll probably want to go explore other planets. For that, you'll need to build a §5warp core§r on your space station, in order to convert it to a §astarship§r. This is about as cool as it sounds, but unfortunately, it's also expensive. You'll also need a §5warp controller§r and some §5dilithium crystals §rin order to jet around the cosmos.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Fuckin' Magnets, Here's How They Work
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
While Fission is great fun, and a good brain puzzler to boot, I think we all know what we're here for.

§2§lVAST PLUMES OF HOT SHRIEKING PLASMA
§c§lHEAT LIKE THE SUN ITSELF
§6§lINTENSE FUEL MANAGEMENT

§rFusion power!

But compared to fusion, the setup for Fission begins to look like stacking wood for your average campfire.  To begin with, we need a way to contain that aforementioned §c§ovast shrieking plasma §rsuch that it doesn't, yknow, leak and murder everything we are and love.


The actual management core can come later,§5 let's work together on the electromagnetic containment structure.

So, nuclear actinides huh?

§7§lWell, I, as a book (not bitter), have no DNA to fuck up.

§rBut §oyou?§r

Pally, that stuff is known as something awful for a reason.

So unless you wanna feel like a hypothetical NATO infantryman in the '83 Fulda Gap, you best get yourself the needed protection for this stuff.

§5Get you that juicy suit, if only cause it's yellow.

This world weirds me out more and more every goddamn day man.

Y'see, I'm pretty sure we mined stuff here.  Like, to the point of exhaustion in some places.


Now though, after last night it's like all new ore-bearing rock just popped outta nowhere.

§9§oClearly, this is a sign.   A sign that we shall triumph.

§fAnd by that I mean t§6§friumph over your laziness you shlub.   It's been ages since I could needlessly demand you dig for random crap to do more of the things that are there to do.   You think I'm passing this up?  Hell no!


Okay, I'm not §othat §rharsh.

§5§lGet ye the new fruits of this weird, conpuzzling planet thing, and we shall do wonders together.

§c§lAdmit it.  You turned to this page expecting an easy out of context own goal about tall black things scaring me.


§rThat being said, the teleporting spawns of not-quite-hell itself do exhibit weird properties, and it seems with those grains I found from your ore remains, we can use it to make a whole new class of machinery and §oCool Shit§*

§b
You know what to do already, you've probably already started you impatient goblin!

§5§lGet ye some enderriffic machinery, let us rule the world through terror and fear of enclosed spaces!

While you're joking about in space, you may realize you still need power.


And while you could rebuild the means of producing it, you could also use this giant spacey place to make it in an all new cool way.


§oMicrowaves!


§6Nuke your base like you nuke your food!§r


§5Get you some stuff and I'll chip right in. §r We'll have a good system of satellite power for any outpost in no time.

§9§lWell, maybe it's faster than either of us thought.

§rOr maybe I'm just a bit of a hurry boy.   Regardless, it's time to get the materials to actually do the smashing.  With the stuff we have and a good pile of resources, we should now be able to make the necessary parts for a functioning fission reactor!


When you're ready to go with all your pieces, a fission reactor is a cube with the edges shaved off, kinda blocky spheroid-ish.  You'll need means of both fuel and cooling, whether active or passive.  Redstone can cycle these things if you need to keep meltdowns (they bad yo) from happening.

But that's already ahead of ourselves: §l§5GET YE THE STUFF.  Make some Fission reactor parts, and I will even directly contribute.
What is this strange world we live in now?
Wait, you did WHAT to my house?
Steel! Coal! Steam! Electricity!
It's all a little more complex and differentiated.
For the world we lost, for the world we have.
The expansion of knowledge, without the worry of impending doom.
